<h1>About Us</h1>

<div class="light">
        We are a group of Christians meeting and serving the Lord together as a local church belonging to Christ (Rom. 16:16; Acts 9:31; Matt. 16:18). We humbly strive to carry out God’s eternal plan for His church where we live (1 Tim. 3:15; Eph. 3:10; 1 Pet. 2:4-5). We have only the scriptures to guide our faith and work. (2 Tim. 3:16-17; 1 Peter 4:11; Acts 20:32; Rom. 10:17) We are determined to worship and work together according to the instructions found in the word of Christ. (Matt. 28:18-20; John 4:23-24; 1 Cor. 14:37) We do not employ in our worship or our work methods or means which God has not commanded us to use. (1 Cor. 3:11; 1 Tim. 1:3; 2 Cor. 4:6-7; II John 1:9) It is our great privilege to be called into the body of Christ and have a place of service with His saints. (Eph. 1:22-23; 2:16-22; 4:11-16; 1 Pet. 2:9-10)
        <br />
        <br />
        We invite any and all to join us in the worship of our great God and obedient service to the glorious calling of the gospel of Jesus Christ. (2 Thess. 2:14-15)
