        What to expect:
        <br />
        <br />
        In our worship we do our best to honor God as He has demonstrated we should in the New Testament. (John 4:24; Heb. 8:4-6; )
        <br />
        <br />
        A typical Sunday morning begins with prayer and Bible study at 9 am. In the next hour, we pray, sing (acapella), read the scriptures, preach, observe the Lord’s Supper, and take up a voluntary collection from the members of the church. (1 Timothy 2:8; Eph. 5:19; 1 Timothy 4:13; 1 Cor. 11:23-28; Acts 20:7; 1 Cor. 16:1-2)    
